  "body": "As a result of [this issue](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/issues/4307) we were told that setting `--JsonRpc.GasCap 0` is problematic.\r\n\r\nWe see on the Geth documentation for [`rpc.gascap`](https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/interface/command-line-options) that it `sets a cap on gas that can be used in eth_call/estimateGas (0=infinite) (default: 50000000)`.\r\n\r\nWhy would the behavior for this be different on Nethermind that we cannot set it to 0 (infinite)?",
